        <p style="font-size:1.4em">The Virtual Research Environment (VirES)</p>
        <p>
          VirES for Aeolus is a highly interactive data manipulation and retrieval interface for <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Observing_the_Earth/Aeolus/Introducing_Aeolus">ESA's Aeolus mission</a> baseline products, officially released by the European Space Agency. It includes tools for studying various atmospheric parameters, in space and time, measured by the Aeolus satellite.
        </p>
        <p>
          VirES for Aeolus allows the interactive, online examination and analysis of the Aeolus datasets, utilizing VirES' peculiar filtering and subsetting mechanisms. <br>
        </p>
        <p>
          <b>Detailed tutorial slides can be accessed <a href="/eoxs_static/other/Vires_Aeolus_Tutorial.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</b>
        </p>
    <p style="font-size:1.4em">Data</p>
        <p>
          The data accessible on VirES consists of the newest baseline products available and any new data will appear within 4 hours of generation.
        </p>
        <p>
          The following Aeolus derived baselines products are availabe:
        </p>
        <p>
          <ul>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              L1B products (e.g. Preliminary HLOS wind observations)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              L2A products (e.g. Geo-located consolidated backscatter and extinction profiles)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              L2B products (e.g. Geo-located consolidated HLOS wind observations, after applying atmospheric corrections)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              L2C products
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              AUX MRC, AUX RRC products (Mie/Rayleigh response calibration)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              AUX ISR products (Instrument Spectral Registration) 
            </li>
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              AUX ZWC (Zero-Wind Calibration)
            </li>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              AUX_MET products (meteorological information)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
          The relevant documentation for each of the products can be downloaded from the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="http://earth.esa.int/aos/AeolusCalVal">Aeolus Calibration and Validation site</a>, at section "Aeolus test dataset access, software tools and product documentation".
        </p>
        <p>
          In addition:
          <ul>
            <li style="list-style-type: circle;">
              The <b>ADAM products</b> have been collected from the ADAM database ( <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="http://adam.noveltis.com/">adam.noveltis.com</a> ), and were produced by the ADAM team under the European Space Agency (ESA) study contract Nr C4000102979. 
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>

